3. Evolution Itself Uses the Same Trick

Biology runs the same strategy.

Instead of one perfect organism, evolution produces many variations.

Then selection pressure determines what survives.

Structure:

variation
↓
environmental test
↓
selection
↓
adaptation

Diversity allows systems to explore possibility space.

If everything were identical, one bad change could wipe everything out.

