7. The Paradox

Here’s the interesting twist.

The system works best when:
	•	each perspective is somewhat competent
	•	but also different enough to make different mistakes.

Too much similarity → errors correlate → system collapses.

Too much chaos → no convergence.

The sweet spot is structured diversity.

